came by the bookstore today.

284
00:14:17,600 --> 00:14:19,700
They were asking
about you.

285
00:14:19,700 --> 00:14:21,600
I figured
diana would be worried.

286
00:14:21,600 --> 00:14:23,700
How did she look?

287
00:14:23,700 --> 00:14:26,400
Okay, i guess.

288
00:14:26,400 --> 00:14:28,400
A little sick.

289
00:14:28,400 --> 00:14:32,100
Kevin, i felt bad
seeing her.

290
00:14:32,100 --> 00:14:33,900
I don't like
what we're doing to her...

291
00:14:33,900 --> 00:14:34,400
what i'm doing to her.

292
00:14:34,400 --> 00:14:36,100
I don't like it
much, either,

293
00:14:36,300 --> 00:14:41,700
but we are on the cusp
of changing the world...

294
00:14:41,700 --> 00:14:43,500
for the better.

295
00:14:43,500 --> 00:14:45,800
We have to keep going,
even if it gets ugly.

296
00:14:45,800 --> 00:14:47,400
Kevin, it's already ugly.

297
00:14:47,400 --> 00:14:49,000
Someone shot you yesterday.

298
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:50,200
I know,

299
00:14:50,200 --> 00:14:52,200
but the experiment

300
00:14:52,200 --> 00:14:55,400
is worth the risk.

301
00:14:55,400 --> 00:14:57,500
They woke me up
to do this.

302
00:14:57,500 --> 00:15:01,200
You woke me up
to do this.

303
00:15:01,200 --> 00:15:04,900
I have to move forward.

304
00:15:04,900 --> 00:15:07,800
And to do that,
i need diana.

305
00:15:11,400 --> 00:15:13,600
And i need you.

306
00:15:33,100 --> 00:15:35,000
Is shawn farrell around?

307
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:36,400
I have something for him.

308
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:40,500
Oh!

309
00:15:40,500 --> 00:15:42,000
I played that

310
00:15:42,000 --> 00:15:43,900
when we were recording
my first album.

311
00:15:43,900 --> 00:15:45,200
I've been holding onto it
for years.

312
00:15:45,200 --> 00:15:48,200
You're really
giving this to me?

313
00:15:48,200 --> 00:15:50,400
You saved my life.

314
00:15:50,400 --> 00:15:52,600
Seems like a fair trade
to me.

315
00:15:57,600 --> 00:16:00,700
So this, uh,
ability of yours...

316
00:16:00,700 --> 00:16:03,500
it works every time
out of the gate?

317
00:16:03,500 --> 00:16:05,200
Yeah, pretty much.

318
00:16:05,200 --> 00:16:06,500
Oh, my god.

319
00:16:06,500 --> 00:16:07,800
I wish
they brought you back

320
00:16:07,800 --> 00:16:09,100
15 years ago.

321
00:16:09,100 --> 00:16:12,200
A career in rock 'n' roll...

322
00:16:12,200 --> 00:16:17,300
sometimes it feels like
you're living in a war zone.

323
00:16:17,300 --> 00:16:19,000
You lose a lot of people
along the way.

324
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:21,700
One day you look up,

325
00:16:21,700 --> 00:16:24,500
and you're the last man
standing.

326
00:16:24,500 --> 00:16:26,600
You should take better care
of yourself.

327
00:16:26,600 --> 00:16:28,800
I'm not always around.

328
00:16:28,800 --> 00:16:31,100
I feel like i owe you
more than a guitar.

329
00:16:31,100 --> 00:16:33,400
We're playing tomorrow night

330
00:16:33,400 --> 00:16:35,400
and i wanted to invite you
backstage.

331
00:16:35,400 --> 00:16:37,100
You can hang out,

332
00:16:37,100 --> 00:16:38,900
watch the show
from the wings.

333
00:16:38,900 --> 00:16:40,300
Really?
Sure.

334
00:16:40,300 --> 00:16:42,600
I figure it'll be handy
having you around.

335
00:16:42,600 --> 00:16:43,800
If i keel over,

336
00:16:43,800 --> 00:16:45,200
