dr. Burkhoff's computers.

364
00:18:36,400 --> 00:18:38,700
Uh, you okay?

365
00:18:38,700 --> 00:18:40,300
I heard
you had the flu.

366
00:18:40,300 --> 00:18:41,600
Hey.

367
00:18:41,600 --> 00:18:42,700
I thought
you were taking a sick day.

368
00:18:42,700 --> 00:18:43,800
Would everyone please

369
00:18:43,800 --> 00:18:45,100
stop treating me
like a plague patient?

370
00:18:45,100 --> 00:18:46,300
I'm fine.

371
00:18:46,300 --> 00:18:47,500
Have we learned anything
here?

372
00:18:47,500 --> 00:18:50,000
Dr. Burkhoff's computers
are clean.

373
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:51,700
Like, completely clean.

374
00:18:51,700 --> 00:18:54,600
I mean, there're no saved files,
no records of anything.

375
00:18:54,600 --> 00:18:56,200
It's like someone
took out his hard drives

376
00:18:56,200 --> 00:18:57,500
and swapped them
for new ones.

377
00:18:57,500 --> 00:18:59,900
So either he took them
somewhere...

378
00:18:59,900 --> 00:19:00,900
or someone else has them.

379
00:19:00,900 --> 00:19:01,900
Diana.

380
00:19:03,600 --> 00:19:05,200
Look at this.

381
00:19:05,200 --> 00:19:06,600
Is that...

382
00:19:06,600 --> 00:19:08,500
kevin?

383
00:19:08,500 --> 00:19:10,100
Yeah.

384
00:19:10,100 --> 00:19:11,400
My god.

385
00:19:11,400 --> 00:19:13,500
These are the side effects
of the injections?

386
00:19:13,500 --> 00:19:14,800
I haven't seen him
in a couple of weeks.

387
00:19:14,800 --> 00:19:16,500
I had no idea
he'd gotten so bad.

388
00:19:16,500 --> 00:19:18,500
Think it's a self-portrait?
No way.

389
00:19:18,500 --> 00:19:19,900
Kevin's hands
weren't steady enough

