cut back on his drinking.

453
00:22:23,300 --> 00:22:25,400
He finally
tried some.

454
00:22:25,400 --> 00:22:26,800
I guess
he overdid it, huh?

455
00:22:26,800 --> 00:22:28,500
It's the same thing
he does with everything.

456
00:22:28,500 --> 00:22:30,500
He insisted on coming here
instead of the hospital.

457
00:22:35,300 --> 00:22:38,500
Do your worst.

458
00:22:40,000 --> 00:22:42,900
Please?

459
00:22:46,700 --> 00:22:48,200
Come to my arms,

460
00:22:48,200 --> 00:22:50,600
my beamish boy.

461
00:22:50,600 --> 00:22:52,600
Lie down. Lie down.

462
00:22:55,000 --> 00:22:57,700
You're my little lifeline.

463
00:23:40,600 --> 00:23:41,700
Kevin.

464
00:23:41,700 --> 00:23:43,300
Dr. Burkhoff,

465
00:23:43,300 --> 00:23:44,700
i've been worried about you.

466
00:23:44,700 --> 00:23:47,900
What are you doing,
hiding up here?

467
00:23:47,900 --> 00:23:49,300
My god.

468
00:23:49,300 --> 00:23:50,800
Look at you.

469
00:23:50,800 --> 00:23:52,300
Dr. Burkhoff,

470
00:23:52,300 --> 00:23:53,900
you need to
come with us.

471
00:23:53,900 --> 00:23:55,500
We're going to get you
some help.

472
00:23:55,500 --> 00:23:56,600
I can't do that.

473
00:23:56,600 --> 00:23:57,800
People are trying
to kill me.

474
00:23:57,800 --> 00:23:58,700
What people?

475
00:23:58,700 --> 00:23:59,700
Who's trying
to kill you?

476
00:23:59,700 --> 00:24:01,500
I think they work
for the government.

477
00:24:01,500 --> 00:24:03,200
They don't work
for ntac.

478
00:24:03,200 --> 00:24:04,300
Are you sure
about that?

479
00:24:04,300 --> 00:24:05,400
Because i'm not.

480
00:24:05,400 --> 00:24:06,500
Listen, kevin.

481
00:24:06,500 --> 00:24:07,600
You know us.

482
00:24:07,600 --> 00:24:08,700
